This ChangeLog was begun on 2004-06-28. <p>
<ol>
<li>
<a href="#head-2473e96bc614a911821242119918a241a41836d6">Introduction</a></li>
<li>
<a href="#head-48d8c627be3c12fac8a0a9ddb9ceaa5e126cf358">Goals</a></li>
<li>
<a href="#head-335bccb6ef7475a27422a859c2d492551aed6dab">Changelog entry format</a></li>
<li>
<a href="#head-8aa57de6dce6ee1c35c6aba7426503281876b258">Changes</a></li>
<li>
<a href="#head-f5a3892d9989866ce6d224333b95a07f718566e2">To Do Lists</a></li>
</ol>

 
</p>
<h2 id="head-2473e96bc614a911821242119918a241a41836d6"><a href="#bottom"><img src="./wiki/starshine/img/moin-bottom.png" alt="[BOTTOM]" height="10" width="14"></a><a href="#top"><img src="./wiki/starshine/img/moin-top.png" alt="[TOP]" height="10" width="14"></a>Introduction</h2>
<a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a>: The foundation text of <a href="./Documentation">Documentation</a> is the in-game help from ToME 2.2.7. <p>
I began this changelog after having worked on the documentation for several days. I will attempt to play catch-up with what I have already done, but I may miss some things. A concrete diff can be obtained by comparison of the doc files here with the in-game help files from ToME 2.2.7, though you'll get a lot of junk in the diff as a result of differences in formatting. 
</p>
<p>
If you notice errors or inconsistencies, please either correct them and note the change here under <em>specific changes</em>, or note the problem in <a class="nonexistent" href="./Documentation_2fDiscussion">Documentation/Discussion</a>. Thanks! 
</p>
<h2 id="head-48d8c627be3c12fac8a0a9ddb9ceaa5e126cf358"><a href="#bottom"><img src="./wiki/starshine/img/moin-bottom.png" alt="[BOTTOM]" height="10" width="14"></a><a href="#top"><img src="./wiki/starshine/img/moin-top.png" alt="[TOP]" height="10" width="14"></a>Goals</h2>
Overall: Make the documentation more helpful, organized, easier to read, and current, while eliminating spoilers. 
    <ol type="1">

    <li>
<p>
Make the help more...helpful. 
</p>
</li>

        <ol type="1">

        <li>
<p>
Improve readability 
</p>
</li>

            <ol type="1">

            <li>
<p>
Reorganize the tree and/or munge and/or rewrite as needed to clarify existing content. 
</p>
</li>
            <li>
<p>
Correct grammar and spelling; reduce wordiness. 
</p>
</li>

            </ol>


        <li>
<p>
Introduce wiki TOCs, headings and other wiki formatting wherever possible in order to improve readability and browsability. Tables only for tables. 
</p>
</li>
        <li>
<p>
Remove outdated material and update with current information wherever possible. 
</p>
</li>
        <li>
<p>
Add relevant non-spoily examples to clarify information given. 
</p>
</li>

        </ol>


    <li>
<p>
Remove spoilers. 
</p>
</li>

        <ol type="1">

        <li>
<p>
Remove game-specific spoilers. 
</p>
</li>
        <li>
<p>
Remove references to Angband and/or other roguelikes. 
</p>
</li>

        </ol>


    <li>
<p>
Do all of this while tracking changes very very carefully, so poor <a href="./FearofFours">FearofFours</a> doesn't blow a gasket trying to keep up with it all. 
</p>
</li>

    </ol>


<h2 id="head-335bccb6ef7475a27422a859c2d492551aed6dab"><a href="#bottom"><img src="./wiki/starshine/img/moin-bottom.png" alt="[BOTTOM]" height="10" width="14"></a><a href="#top"><img src="./wiki/starshine/img/moin-top.png" alt="[TOP]" height="10" width="14"></a>Changelog entry format</h2>
A good changelog entry contains: 
    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 your name 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 name of the page you changed 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 what change(s) you made, <em>in detail</em>. This isn't just a random document. The actual ToME documentation is being modified from this page! If you get a huge list of changes, put something like 'major rewrite', but it helps to point out things even then. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 why you changed it (if relevant) 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 the @<strong></strong>TIME@ 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


